On Sunday, November 15, about six fully armed men reportedly abducted Eno Patrick Orok, the wife of a former House of Representatives member in Cross River, Patrick Orok Agbor.  One of the daughters of the former lawmaker who served in Akampka constituency from 1999 to 2003 spoke about the development this morning. Her words; “Good morning. Please, my mother, Eno Patrick Orok, was kidnapped Sunday, at about 10 pm from our home, at Uyanga, Akamkpa LGA. About 6 gunmen, fully armed with face masks, forced themselves into our compound and abducted her. “She is about 60 years old. Works at Federal Training Institute Calabar, besides Roadsafety office Marian”, she told Vanguard.  Source Maiduguri -  Mrs Aisha Buhari, the Wife of the President, on Sunday presented about N30 million cash support to parents of the abducted Government Secondary School (GSS) Chibok students in Borno. Buhari, represented by Hajiya Nana Shettima, the wife of the Borno governor presented the cash to the parents at… July 3, 2016 In "News" ENUGU -  The Women for Peace and Justice, South East Zone, on Tuesday held a prayer rally seeking God’s intervention for the safe release of the girls abducted three weeks ago from Chibok, Borno State. The women carried placards with inscriptions `Freedom of the girls is all we want’, `Bring… May 6, 2014 In "News" Gunmen, who abducted the wife of the Anglican Bishop of Ikeduru Diocese in Imo State, Anuri Maduwuike, had set her free, Punch Metro reports. Anuri Maduwuike She was released after an undisclosed amount of money was purportedly paid as ransom. The Bishop’s wife who was waylaid and abducted on Friday… August 26, 2019 In "Metro"